<section role="openmfg">
  <title>List Return Authorizations</title>
  <para></para>
  <para><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/openReturnAuthorizations.png" />
        </imageobject>
        <caption>List Return Authorizations</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para>When displaying open Return Authorizations, you are presented with the
  following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry role="openmfg">
      <term>All Warehouses</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to display a list of open Sales Orders for all
        Warehouses.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry role="openmfg">
      <term>Selected</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Specify Warehouse whose open Sales Orders you want to
        display.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Show Expired</term>
      <listitem>
        <para></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Return Authorizations</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Display lists open Sales Orders.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Automatically Update</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Select to automatically update the display every five
        minutes.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>To the far right of the screen, the following buttons are
  available:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>CLOSE</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
        desktop.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>PRINT</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>NEW</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Opens screen for creating a new Return Authorization.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>EDIT</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersEDIT">
        <para id="openReturnAuthorizationsEDIT">Enables you to edit
        highlighted Return Authorizations. The edit screen is the same as that
        for creating a new Return Authorization--except that when editing, the
        fields will contain Return Authorization information. Double-clicking
        on a Return Authorization will also bring you to the editing
        screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>VIEW</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersVIEW">
        <para id="openReturnAuthorizationsVIEW">Highlight a Return
        Authorization and then select this button to reach a read-only view of
        the "Edit" screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>DELETE</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersDELETE">
        <para id="openReturnAuthorizationsDELETE">Highlight a Return
        Authorization and then select this button to remove the Return
        Authorization from the master list</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>Right-clicking on a Return Authorization in the Return Authorizations
  list enables you to select from the following menu options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Edit</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersEDIT">
        <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                    xpointer="element(openReturnAuthorizationsEDIT)" />
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>View</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersVIEW">
        <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                    xpointer="element(openReturnAuthorizationsVIEW)" />
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Delete</term>
      <listitem id="openSalesOrdersDELETE">
        <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                    xpointer="element(openReturnAuthorizationsDELETE)" />
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <xi:include href="../supportfiles/rightclick.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                xpointer="element(rightclickPrintReturnAuthForm)" />
    <xi:include href="../widgets/xtreewidget.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                xpointer="element(xtreewidget.menu.exportcontents)" />
  </variablelist>
  <para></para>
